    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"id\":\"m001\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Budget vs Actual Variance Analysis\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Project Overview\\n\",\"This notebook analyzes budget and actual spending or revenue across departments and periods to identify meaningful variances and likely explanations.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\"- Calculate budget variance (dollar and percentage) across departments.\\n\",\"- Identify favorable and unfavorable variances.\\n\",\"- Visualize variance patterns over time.\\n\",\"- Generate management-ready variance commentary.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Business / Research Problem\\n\",\"Without systematic variance analysis, organizations cannot distinguish between planned and unplanned spending changes.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Why This Analysis Matters\\n\",\"Variance analysis is a core financial control mechanism that surfaces overspending early and validates budgeting accuracy.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"id\":\"m002\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Dataset Overview\\n\",\"Synthetic dataset of **monthly budget vs actual data for 6 departments** over 12 months.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\",\"Synthetically generated for educational purposes.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"id\":\"c001\",\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\nfor pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\", \\\"numpy\\\", \\\"matplotlib\\\", \\\"seaborn\\\"]:\\n    try:\\n        importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n    except ImportError:\\n        subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, \\\"-m\\\", \\\"pip\\\", \\\"install\\\", \\\"-q\\\", pkg])\\nprint(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"id\":\"c002\",\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import numpy as np\\nimport pandas as pd\\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\nimport seaborn as sns\\nimport warnings\\nwarnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\nsns.set_style(\\\"whitegrid\\\")\\n%matplotlib inline\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"id\":\"c003\",\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"SEED = 42\\nDEPARTMENTS = [\\\"Engineering\\\", \\\"Sales\\\", \\\"Marketing\\\", \\\"HR\\\", \\\"Finance\\\", \\\"Operations\\\"]\\nMONTHS = list(range(1, 13))\\nprint(\\\"Configuration loaded.\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"id\":\"m003\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Dataset Generation\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"id\":\"c004\",\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"rng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\\n\\nbudget_bases = {\\\"Engineering\\\": 150000, \\\"Sales\\\": 120000, \\\"Marketing\\\": 100000,\\n                \\\"HR\\\": 50000, \\\"Finance\\\": 40000, \\\"Operations\\\": 80000}\\n\\nrows = []\\nfor dept in DEPARTMENTS:\\n    base = budget_bases[dept]\\n    for month in MONTHS:\\n        budget = base + rng.normal(0, base * 0.05)\\n        # Actual varies from budget with some systematic patterns\\n        variance_pct = rng.normal(0.02, 0.08)  # slight overspend bias\\n        actual = budget * (1 + variance_pct)\\n        rows.append({\\\"department\\\": dept, \\\"month\\\": month,\\n                     \\\"budget\\\": round(budget, 2), \\\"actual\\\": round(actual, 2)})\\n\\ndf = pd.DataFrame(rows)\\ndf[\\\"variance\\\"] = df[\\\"actual\\\"] - df[\\\"budget\\\"]\\ndf[\\\"variance_pct\\\"] = df[\\\"variance\\\"] / df[\\\"budget\\\"]\\ndf[\\\"favorable\\\"] = df[\\\"variance\\\"] < 0\\nprint(f\\\"Dataset: {df.shape}\\\")\\ndf.head()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"id\":\"c005\",\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"print(f\\\"Missing: {df.isnull().sum().sum()}, ✅ Validation passed.\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"id\":\"m004\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Variance Analysis\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"id\":\"c006\",\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"dept_summary = df.groupby(\\\"department\\\").agg(\\n    total_budget=(\\\"budget\\\", \\\"sum\\\"),\\n    total_actual=(\\\"actual\\\", \\\"sum\\\"),\\n    avg_variance_pct=(\\\"variance_pct\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n).sort_values(\\\"avg_variance_pct\\\", ascending=False)\\ndept_summary[\\\"total_variance\\\"] = dept_summary[\\\"total_actual\\\"] - dept_summary[\\\"total_budget\\\"]\\nprint(\\\"=== Annual Variance by Department ===\\\")\\ndept_summary.round(0)\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"id\":\"c007\",\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\\n\\ndept_summary[\\\"total_variance\\\"].sort_values().plot(kind=\\\"barh\\\", ax=axes[0],\\n    color=[\\\"#e74c3c\\\" if v > 0 else \\\"#2ecc71\\\" for v in dept_summary[\\\"total_variance\\\"].sort_values()])\\naxes[0].set_title(\\\"Total Variance by Department\\\")\\naxes[0].set_xlabel(\\\"$ Variance (positive = over budget)\\\")\\naxes[0].axvline(0, color=\\\"black\\\", ls=\\\"--\\\")\\n\\n# Monthly variance trend\\nmonthly_var = df.groupby(\\\"month\\\")[\\\"variance\\\"].sum()\\naxes[1].bar(monthly_var.index, monthly_var.values,\\n    color=[\\\"#e74c3c\\\" if v > 0 else \\\"#2ecc71\\\" for v in monthly_var.values])\\naxes[1].set_title(\\\"Monthly Total Variance\\\")\\naxes[1].set_xlabel(\\\"Month\\\")\\naxes[1].axhline(0, color=\\\"black\\\", ls=\\\"--\\\")\\n\\nplt.tight_layout()\\nplt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"id\":\"c008\",\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"# Heatmap of variance % by dept × month\\npivot = df.pivot_table(values=\\\"variance_pct\\\", index=\\\"department\\\", columns=\\\"month\\\")\\nfig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(14, 5))\\nsns.heatmap(pivot, annot=True, fmt=\\\".0%\\\", cmap=\\\"RdYlGn_r\\\", center=0, ax=ax, linewidths=0.5)\\nax.set_title(\\\"Variance % Heatmap: Department × Month\\\")\\nplt.tight_layout()\\nplt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"id\":\"m005\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Key Findings\\n\",\"1. **Most departments show a slight overspend bias** — budgets may need upward adjustment.\\n\",\"2. **Variance is not uniform across months** — some months show systematic overspend.\\n\",\"3. **The heatmap reveals department-specific seasonal patterns.**\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Limitations\\n\",\"- Synthetic data without real organizational context.\\n\",\"- No line-item detail within departments.\\n\",\"- No explanation for why variances occurred.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Recommendations / Next Steps\\n\",\"1. Investigate persistent overspend in specific departments.\\n\",\"2. Adjust budget assumptions based on actual patterns.\\n\",\"3. Implement rolling forecasts to improve accuracy.\\n\",\"4. Set variance thresholds for management alerts.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Common Mistakes\\n\",\"1. Treating all variances as bad — favorable variances can indicate underinvestment.\\n\",\"2. Not distinguishing between timing variances and real overspend.\\n\",\"3. Over-reacting to small percentage variances on small budgets.\\n\",\"4. Not connecting variances to business outcomes.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Mini Challenge\\n\",\"1. Calculate cumulative year-to-date variance by department.\\n\",\"2. Flag months where any department exceeds 10% variance.\\n\",\"3. Simulate the impact of reducing top department variance by 50%.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\",\"- **Variance analysis is essential for financial control.**\\n\",\"- **Visual heatmaps make variance patterns immediately clear.**\\n\",\"- **Both favorable and unfavorable variances deserve investigation.**\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
